						               													<description>You play detective chickens who are looking for turnip thief. All seven suspects are depicted on the game board this is: grandfather, grandmother, granddaughter, dog, cat, mouse and the turnip itself. Next to each suspect lies a round token, on the underside of which it is indicated, who is this character: innocent, kidnapper or accomplice.&amp;#10;Chickens walk around the game board, collecting cards of the investigation: clues, signs and witnesses. If you got a card, you can go to the suspect, present it, tell why it points to this character, and look at his token in secret. When you find the kidnapper, you will have to come to him and bring charges: a motive card and three matching consequence cards. Tell why the attacker stole the turnip, how do you managed to figure him out and whether he had an accomplice. If you do everything right you will win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
